@startuml pipeline_orchestrator
'──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
'  ACR-QA  v4.0.0  —  Pipeline Orchestrator Detail
'  No swimlanes — single-column portrait-friendly activity diagram
'  King Salman International University  ·  CSE494  ·  2025-26
'──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName  "Arial"
skinparam defaultFontSize  10
skinparam shadowing        false

skinparam activity {
  BackgroundColor        #E8EDF4
  BorderColor            #002654
  BorderThickness        2
  FontSize               10
  DiamondBackgroundColor #FFF3BF
  DiamondBorderColor     #C9A84C
}

skinparam arrow {
  Color     #002654
  FontColor #444444
  FontSize  9
  Thickness 1.5
}

skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #FFFDE7
  BorderColor     #C9A84C
  FontSize        9
}

title <color:#002654><b>ACR-QA v4.0.0 — Pipeline Orchestrator (CORE/main.py)</b></color>

start

:⓪  Rate Limit Check  (Redis token bucket)\nPOST /v1/scan → 202 Accepted · run_id returned;

:①  Repository Ingestion\nValidate path · detect languages · apply .acrqa.yml exclusions;

fork
  :Python tools\nRuff · Bandit · Semgrep\nVulture · Radon · jscpd;
fork again
  :JS / TS tools\nESLint-security · Semgrep\nnpm audit · jscpd;
fork again
  :Go tools\ngosec · staticcheck\nSemgrep;
fork again
  :Cross-language\nSecrets Detector\nTruffleHog · Trivy;
end fork

note right : ②  Parallel tool dispatch\nthread pool · stdout captured per tool

:③a  Normalise → CanonicalFinding schema\nconfig filter · scope exclusions (≈15% eliminated before scoring);

:③b  Triage Memory Lookup\nlearned-suppression table · per-repo rules;

:③c  Cross-Tool Deduplication (2-pass)\nlocation hash + rule hash · merge overlapping findings;

:③d  Intra-Procedural Taint Analysis (AST BFS)\nconfidence = max(0.4, 0.95 − 0.1·(h−1))  where h = hop depth;

:③e  Call-Graph Reachability (BFS, max_depth=5)\nentry points: Flask/FastAPI routes · Celery tasks · __main__;

if (finding reachable?) then (yes)
else (no — unreachable / dead code)
  :Apply −20 confidence penalty\nretained for audit · deprioritised in ranking;
endif

:③f  Per-Rule Cap + Sort by confidence descending;

:④  Five-Signal Confidence Scoring\nseverity (40%) · category (20%) · tool_reliability (15%)\nrule_specificity (10%) · fix_validation (10%)\nmulti-tool bonus +5  →  C ∈ [0, 100];

if (C ≥ 30 ?) then (yes)
else (no — soft-suppress)
  :Mark deprioritised = True\nvisible in dashboard, ranked last;
endif

:⑤  RAG Enrichment\ndict_lookup(rule_id) O(1) → Groq LLaMA-3.3-70B × 3 runs\nN-gram entropy filter τ = 3.2 bits\nstore enrichment in llm_explanations (PostgreSQL provenance);

:⑤b  Post-Quantum Attestation\nECDSA-P256 + CRYSTALS-Dilithium3 · Sigstore keyless;

:⑥  Supply Chain Scan + CBoM\npip-audit · npm audit · CVE mapping · 62 cryptographic algorithms\nNIST FIPS 203/204 PQC migration flags;

:⑦  Quality Gate Enforcement\nevaluate .acrqa.yml severity thresholds → PASS / FAIL\nemit gate_result for CI/CD runner;

:⑧  Output Delivery\nJSON · SARIF · Markdown\nGitHub PR inline comments · check-run status\nPostgreSQL: UPDATE run SET status=COMPLETED;

stop

legend top right
  |= Stage Group  |= Role                             |
  |<back:#E8EDF4>  ⓪–①  </back>| Rate limit + Ingestion         |
  |<back:#C8D8F0>  ②–③  </back>| Tool execution + Normalisation |
  |<back:#FFF3BF>  ④–⑤  </back>| Scoring + AI enrichment        |
  |<back:#D3F9D8>  ⑥–⑧  </back>| Supply chain + Gate + Output   |
end legend

@enduml
